    <section id="planning-phase" class="mb-16" aria-labelledby="planning-phase-title">
      <h2 id="planning-phase-title" class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4" style="color: var(--color-text-primary);">Planning Your Renovation</h2>
      <div class="mb-6" style="color: var(--color-text-secondary);">
        Successful renovations start with clear planning. Define your goals, assess current condition, and establish realistic timelines and budgets.
      </div>

      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-3 mt-6" style="color: var(--color-text-primary);">Key Planning Steps:</h3>
      <ol class="space-y-3 list-decimal list-inside" style="color: var(--color-text-secondary);">
        <li><strong>Define your vision:</strong> What's the primary goal? Kitchen function? Bathroom modernization? Home value increase?</li>
        <li><strong>Assess current condition:</strong> Identify underlying issues (plumbing, electrical, structural) that may need addressing.</li>
        <li><strong>Determine scope:</strong> Single room or whole-home? Cosmetic updates or structural work?</li>
        <li><strong>Research local building codes:</strong> Permit requirements vary by municipality and project type.</li>
        <li><strong>Set realistic timeline:</strong> Most renovations take longer than initially expected.</li>
        <li><strong>Plan for contingencies:</strong> Budget 10-20% extra for unexpected issues.</li>
      </ol>

      <div class="rounded-lg border p-4 mt-6 text-sm" style="background-color: var(--color-brand-secondary-tint); border-color: var(--color-border-primary); color: var(--color-brand-secondary);">
        <strong>Pro Tip:</strong> Create a mood board with inspiration images. This helps contractors understand your vision and improves communication throughout the project.
      </div>
    </section>

